Add unpins' uniform `--unpin-program=NAME` multicall selector to busybox.

`busybox --unpin-program=ls [args]` runs the `ls` applet — a synonym of the
native `busybox ls` form, so every catalog multicall is driven the same way
(see docs/multicall.md). It is handled in busybox_main (reached only when the
binary is invoked as `busybox`), so an alias symlink (`ls`, `cat`, …) — which
dispatches on argv[0] in main() and never reaches busybox_main — stays locked
to its argv[0] identity and ignores the flag. The native `busybox <applet>`
form keeps working unchanged.

--- a/libbb/appletlib.c
+++ b/libbb/appletlib.c
@@ -847,6 +847,16 @@
 	}
 #  endif

+	if (is_prefixed_with(argv[1], "--unpin-program=")) {
+		/* unpins' uniform multicall selector: run NAME as the applet,
+		 * mirroring the bare "busybox <applet>" form. An alias symlink
+		 * dispatches on argv[0] in main() and never reaches here, so it
+		 * stays locked to its identity and ignores this flag. */
+		applet_name = argv[1] + (sizeof("--unpin-program=") - 1);
+		argv[1] = (char*)applet_name; /* applet sees argv[0]=NAME */
+		run_applet_and_exit(applet_name, argv + 1);
+	}
+
